text: Darab County () is a county in Fars Province in Iran. The capital of the county is Darab.Gitashenasi Province Atlas of Iran اطلس گیتاشناسی استان‌های ایران At the 2006 census, the county's population was 172,938, in 39,955 families. The county is subdivided into three districts: the Central District, Rostaq District, and Forg District. The county has four cities: Darab, Jannat Shahr, Fadami & Do Borji. * Villages ** bargan ** Abshoor ** Tizab ** Layzangan == References == Category:Counties in Fars Province
